The Red Arrows proved to be a crowd-pleaser at the RAF Cosford Air Show.Thousands flocked to the airfield to watch the aircraft displays, which kicked off with the RAF Falcons, who jumped from their aircraft with their chutes.The Red Arrows took to the sky later Sunday afternoon, trailing their famous red, white and blue smoke.This year's theme was "take flight", with the hope it would kickstart people's enthusiasm in aviation and "potentially a career in the Royal Air Force".
